      },
      "date": "2013-10-25 23:29:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThe patch fixed the problem that I was experiencing with metadata-updates, but I'd like to see it pass in our autotest testing. metadata-updates is not included in the normal tests in autotest.\n\nTo get metadata-updates to run, we need to add the following to the commit message before the Signed-off-by line:\nTest-Parameters: testlist=metadata-updates\n\nThis will allow the normal tests to run, but also include a separate run with testlist tests in it. \n\nI'm happy to resubmit this with the testlist line and will if I don't see movement on this patch in the next day or so.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
